tton></div></div><div class=3D"comment-body expanded"><p><span>Let=E2=80=99=
s say you=E2=80=99re an accountant, you paid a lot of money for those crede=
ntials, in fact your high school guidance counselor specifically recommende=
d that you study in the field.  You were a great student, you=E2=80=99ve go=
t some student loans but nothing that a $20 per hour entry level job couldn=
=E2=80=99t fix.  As a matter of fact you live in a town or city with dozens=
 of banks and brokers and these businesses employ thousands of accountants.=
  You live across the street from an accounting firm that employs hundreds =
of accountants and business is not just good, business is great.  And there=
s an accountant shortage, or so they say.  You graduated at the top of your=
 class and all you want is an entry level foot-in-the-door type job, any of=
 the employers will do.  You want to work and you=E2=80=99re available righ=
t away, all your paperwork and licenses are in order, your references impec=
cable and your work ethic is strong.  You=E2=80=99re willing to work for $1=
4 an hour or anything more than that, and you would even consider a $10 an =
hour job as long as it=E2=80=99s in accounting.  For some reason, you can=
=E2=80=99t get an interview but day after day you see cars pulling up with =
foreign nationals parking and entering the many different  men and women, m=
ost barely speak English entering to work in these places in the city where=
 you live and go to work as accountants.  There=E2=80=99s been one scandal =
after another with these accountants but the company continues to hire more=
, if someone quits, that accountant is replaced with another accountant fro=
m the same country or region.  You=E2=80=99re not seeing very many American=
 accountants and your accounting college friends all report the same troubl=
e finding work.  Sure there=E2=80=99s chipotle.  And it=E2=80=99s not just =
the salsa that=E2=80=99s hot, so are the staff.  It=E2=80=99s a great place=
 to meet someone to date but you really had planned on that accounting thin=
g and don=E2=80=99t understand why it=E2=80=99s so hard to get an accountin=
g job.  That=E2=80=99s what=E2=80=99s going on in a nutshell, don=E2=80=99t=
 be surprised if people don=E2=80=99t jump at the chance to get that chipot=
le job when they see all these unqualified people with questionable credent=
ials getting full employment for jobs that they know would be done faster a=
nd more efficiently if someone would give them an interview.  Doesn=E2=80=
=99t matter what color or ethnicity, pay doesn=E2=80=99t matter, they train=
ed for this marathon and like an Australian shepherd, they want to use thei=
r talents to do something they are very good at.  Sure it=E2=80=99s better =
to be well rounded, maybe this is a very difficult yet important lesson, th=
at life isn=E2=80=99t fair but it seems more fair for some people than othe=
rs, tough lesson to learn.  Hopefully they can exchange their place behind =
a desk for something that will give them fresh air and sunshine and at leas=
t be healthy.  </span></p><div role=3D"button" class=3D"show-all-toggle"><d=
